to the editor a jan 2 news article is right to focus on criticism of the metropolitan transportation authority for its reluctance to move from diesel fueled buses to those powered by compressed natural gas the mta has one of the worst records in the country on converting to natural gas with less than 2 percent of its buses using clean natural gas by contrast 31 other transit authorities have 20 percent or more natural gas fueled buses in their fleets nationally almost a third of all planned bus orders are for natural gas fueled buses with the highest asthma rate and some of the highest air toxicity rates in the country new york residents can no longer afford the mta 's resistance to natural gas technology joanna d underwood new york jan 3 2000 the writer is president of inform an environmental research group

